column3:
Throw your hands in a circle for Miles Blakely, aka Emy Bop, Open Television’s first visual designer. Over the next few months, Miles will work directly with Eli Micky & the Open Television tribe to bring our multimedia campaigns to life! Miles will support our Activation Officer as we upgrade OTV's creative vision with a dash of the bizarre and a sprinkle of divinity. 

Emy was born in Hotlanta, and moved to Chicago to explore his identity and craft. His multimedia art practice includes: animation, short film, digital art, and painting. He has been fortunate to work with brands like Under Armor and Balenciaga as a content creator & video coordinator. Emy uses digital materials to craft new worlds with imagery that challenges the sensory to experience the world in alternative ways. 

Please send love and doves to OTV's newest addition!
SYMBIOTIC EXPLORES TWO DISABLED WOMEN AS THEY TRY TO NAVIGATE THEIR ADULT LIVES AFTER IMPULSIVELY MOVING IN TOGETHER.

Blessing your feed with #OTVPlayback's grand finale! OTV restreams Fck Stan, The Right Swipe, FOBia Series, Kings and Queens, Symbiotic, Just Call Me Ripley, and Renee. The party begins Friday at 6 pm CST.

THEIR RELATIONSIP WITH EACH OTHER AND EVERYONE AROUND THEM ARE TESTED AS THEY TRY TO BECOME THE BEST PERFORMERS IN THE MOST COMPETITIVE DRAG SCENE IN THE COUNTRY.
AN INDIAN IMMIGRANT WOMAN ADAPTS TO LIFE IN AMERICA WITH HER AMERICAN ROOMMATE AND INDIAN NEIGHBOR WHILE DEALING WITH CULTURAL MISUNDERSTANDINGS AND GENERAL MAYHEM IN FOBIA.

Blessing your feed with #OTVPlayback's grand finale!  OTV restreams Fck Stan, The Right Swipe, FOBia Series, Kings and Queens, Symbiotic, Just Call Me Ripley, and Renee. The party begins Friday at  6 pm CST.
